{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Dev fee is double-counted, minting reflected balance to the contract on every taxed transfer","locations":["0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:873","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1181","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1221","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1237","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1251"],"claim":"The constructor enables an 8% team/dev fee, but `_getRValues()` subtracts only the reflection fee from the recipient's reflected amount and never subtracts the dev fee. `_takeCharity()` still credits the full dev fee to `address(this)`, so each taxed transfer creates extra reflected balance for the contract instead of sourcing those tokens from the sender's transfer amount.","impact":"The contract accumulates synthetic tokens that were never actually debited from the transfer, then sells them for real ETH through the auto-swap path and forwards proceeds to the team wallet. This breaks token accounting and can continuously extract value from the AMM and holders.","paths":["Any buy after trading opens where fees are active","Any sell where fees are active","Any wallet-to-wallet transfer between non-fee-exempt addresses while `_teamDev` remains nonzero"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cooldown is keyed by `sender`, enabling a market-wide 60 second buy denial of service","locations":["0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:680","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:708","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:713","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1069"],"claim":"The cooldown updates `_lastTx[sender]`. On buys, the token transfer is from `uniswapV2Pair` to the buyer, so the first successful buy sets `_lastTx[uniswapV2Pair] = block.timestamp + 60 seconds`. Every later buy during that window reverts, regardless of buyer.","impact":"Any attacker can keep the market's buy side frozen indefinitely with a dust buy roughly once per minute, monopolizing access and creating a permissionless market-wide denial of service.","paths":["Buyer A purchases from the pair, setting cooldown on `uniswapV2Pair`","Buyer B attempts another buy within 60 seconds and hits the cooldown revert","An attacker repeats small buys to keep all other buys blocked"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Owner can blacklist the LP pair and freeze all trading","locations":["0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:708","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1001","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1057","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1058"],"claim":"`RemoveSniper()` forbids blacklisting only the router, not `uniswapV2Pair`. If the owner blacklists the pair, sells revert because `recipient == uniswapV2Pair`, and buys revert because the token transfer is called by the pair so `msg.sender == uniswapV2Pair`.","impact":"The owner has an immediate hard-stop lever over the market and can trap liquidity and holders by permanently freezing both buys and sells.","paths":["Owner calls `RemoveSniper(uniswapV2Pair)`","Any sell reverts because the recipient pair is blacklisted","Any buy reverts because `msg.sender` is the blacklisted pair"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Ownership can be made to look renounced and later reclaimed","locations":["0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:455","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:456","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:457","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:463","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:467"],"claim":"`lock()` sets the owner to the zero address but stores the former owner in `_previousOwner`, and `unlock()` later restores full ownership to that stored address after the lock period. This creates a hidden reclaim path that can make the contract appear ownerless without actually removing admin control.","impact":"Users can be misled into trusting the token as renounced while the same controller retains the ability to later recover privileged functions such as blacklist management, swap controls, and fee-wallet changes.","paths":["Owner calls `lock(time)` so `owner()` returns zero","Users treat the contract as renounced or ownerless","After `_lockTime`, the previous owner calls `unlock()` and regains all admin powers"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Forced full-balance auto-swaps use `amountOutMin = 0`, making them trivially sandwichable","locations":["0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1097","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1100","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1123","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1132","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1134"],"claim":"When the contract's token balance reaches the threshold, the next non-buy transfer triggers a market sale of the contract's entire token balance. The swap uses `swapExactTokensForETHSupportingFeeOnTransferTokens(..., amountOutMin = 0, ...)`, so it accepts any execution price.","impact":"MEV searchers can predict and sandwich these forced sells, worsening execution for the contract and extracting value from fee proceeds and the user transaction that triggers the swap.","paths":["Wait until `balanceOf(address(this)) >= _numOfTokensToExchangeForTeamDev`","Observe a non-buy transfer in the mempool","Front-run to push price down, let the contract sell at any price, then back-run the recovery"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"A reverting or gas-heavy team wallet can turn auto-swap into a sell-side denial of service","locations":["0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1100","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1106","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1141","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1142","0x31a4f372aa891b46ba44dc64be1d8947c889e9c6/Contract.sol:1304"],"claim":"The owner can arbitrarily change `_teamDevAddress`, and the transfer path forwards ETH with Solidity `transfer()`, which reverts if the recipient contract rejects ETH or needs more than 2300 gas. Once auto-swap is triggered, that reverting ETH send reverts the whole token transfer.","impact":"After the contract reaches the swap threshold, sells and normal transfers can become impossible until the owner intervenes, creating a realistic buy-only or frozen-market condition.","paths":["Owner sets `_teamDevAddress` to a contract that reverts on receiving ETH or needs more than 2300 gas","The contract accumulates enough tokens to trigger auto-swap","Any non-buy transfer hits `sendETHToTeamDev()` and reverts"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Owner can drain all tokens via manualSwap","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`manualSwap()` only swaps tokens already held by the contract from fees; it does not let the owner seize arbitrary user balances. This is an admin fee-handling function, not a separate exploit."},{"title":"Owner can change charity wallet to steal funds","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Changing the fee recipient is an explicit owner-controlled parameter of the fee system. By itself this is centralization/trust risk, not an unintended vulnerability distinct from the retained-admin findings."},{"title":"Sniper list can be abused to block any address","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Overstated as written: `_transfer()` checks `recipient` and `msg.sender`, not `sender`, so a blacklisted holder can still move tokens out via `transferFrom` through a non-blacklisted spender such as the router. The stronger pair-freeze variant is retained separately."},{"title":"Transaction limits can be fully removed by owner","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`_maxTxAmount` is never enforced anywhere in `_transfer()`, so changing or removing it has no effect and does not introduce a new exploit path."},{"title":"UniswapOnly restriction can be disabled","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`_removeDestLimit()` is an explicit owner toggle for an anti-bot restriction. Disabling that restriction is an intended admin action, not a standalone vulnerability."},{"title":"Reflection rate calculation may underflow","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The cited `rSupply < _rTotal.div(_tTotal)` check is the standard RFI-style fallback guard in `_getCurrentSupply()`. No concrete underflow or exploitable mis-accounting was demonstrated from this condition itself."},{"title":"Missing event logs for critical functions","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Missing events are a transparency issue, but not a realistic protocol-level vulnerability causing theft, insolvency, lockup, or denial of service."},{"title":"Division in reflection calculation may lose precision","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Integer truncation on fee calculations is expected Solidity behavior and does not create meaningful exploitable harm here."},{"title":"Block timestamp can be manipulated by miner","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"This is a generic blockchain property and does not materially change the already-retained cooldown flaw or create a separate reportable issue in this contract."}]}
